Upon her return to Quebec City in 1920, Dompierre continued her career as a concert pianist; appearing with every numerous important ensembles and at major venues throughout Canada.
Lucille Dompierre (1899 – 1968) was a Canadian pianist and arranger.
For many years she was the resident pianist of the Quebec Symphony Orchestra.
